# Next.js Data Mutation Constraints

Handle all form submissions and data mutations through Next.js Server Actions with optimistic updates.

- ALWAYS execute data mutations through Next.js Server Actions.
- NEVER use client-side `fetch` calls to internal API routes for form submission or state mutation.
- Define Server Actions in a separate file with the `"use server"` directive or inline in a Server Component.
- For user-triggered mutations, ALWAYS pair the Server Action with `useOptimistic`.
- Update UI immediately through optimistic state while the Server Action resolves in the background.
